Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat
oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Trim
@green beans{6%ounce} if necessary.

In a #small bowl{}, combine half the @sour cream{4%tablespoon} (you'll use the
rest later), @Frank's Seasoning Blend{1/2%tsp}, and a big pinch of
@salt{pinch}. (Be sure to measure the Frank's Seasoning—you'll use the rest in
the next step.) Stir in @water{1%tsp} 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a
drizzling consistency.

Place @butter{1%tbsp} in a #medium microwave-safe bowl{}; microwave until
melted, ~{30-45%seconds}.

Stir in @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, @Monterey Jack cheese{1/4%cup}, remaining
@Frank's Seasoning Blend{6.7%g}, and a big pinch of @salt{pinch} and
@pepper{pinch}.

Dice @Yukon Gold potatoes{12%ounce} into 1/2-inch pieces. Place in a #medium
pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil; cook
until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. Reserve 1/2 cup potato cooking liquid, then
drain.

Add a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} and scallion whites to empty #pot{} over
low heat; cook until softened, ~{1%minute}.

Return drained potatoes to pot; mash with remaining sour cream and
@butter{1%tbsp} until smooth and creamy, adding splashes of reserved potato
cooking liquid as needed. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While potatoes cook, pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and
season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Place on one side of a lightly oiled
#baking sheet{}. (For 4 servings, spread chicken out across entire sheet.)

Mound tops of chicken with panko mixture, pressing firmly to adhere (no need to
coat the undersides).

Toss green beans on opposite side of sheet from chicken with a large drizzle of
@olive oil{2%teaspoon} and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. (For 4
servings, toss green beans on a second sheet. Roast chicken on top rack and
green beans on middle rack.)

Roast on top rack until chicken is golden brown and cooked through and green
beans are tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. TIP: If green beans are done before chicken,
remove from sheet and continue roasting chicken.

Transfer roasted green beans to a #large bowl{}; toss with @butter{1%tbsp} until
melted.

Divide green beans, potatoes, and chicken between plates. Drizzle chicken with
creamy Buffalo sauce and @honey{2%teaspoon} (or serve both on the side for
dipping). Garnish potatoes with scallion greens and serve.

> Are you the type of person who only goes to game nights on the off chance
> that Buffalo wings will be served? This dish is a slam dunk with Buffalo-spiced
> chicken, buttery roasted green beans, and creamy scallion mashed potatoes on
> the side!